parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake cable holder can cause the cables to hang and rub against the driveshaft, leading to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Rattle sound from the chassis
park brake cable holder broken
cables hanging and rubbing against the driveshaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal pad can cause the pedal to slip off, leading to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal pad came off
indentations on the bottom left of the pad
pedal slipped off while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause a loss of braking power, increased stopping distance, and accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal felt soft or spongy
brake pedal stuck to the floor
brake pedal did not return to its normal position
vehicle was unable to stop without the use of the emergency brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause a loss of power brake assist, leading to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal felt like pushing down on cement
brake pedal did not act normally while braking
vehicle was unable to stop without the use of the emergency brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the ABS and cruise control systems to fail, leading to a loss of braking power and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights came on
including dynamic stability control and ABS warning lights
ABS and cruise control systems failed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Left Rear Brake and Turn Light Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the left rear brake and turn lights can cause a safety hazard, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The left rear brake light and turn signal are not functioning
the warning message appears on the dashboard
the light bulbs need to be replaced
the metal pins in the connector are melted and stuck into the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a head-on collision can cause serious injury or even death, as the driver and passengers are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in a head-on collision
the driver sustained a mild concussion when their head hit the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the FEM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including the brake lights, turn signals, and airbags, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The FEM keeps getting wet and failing
causing various electrical systems to malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seatbelt and door locks can cause a safety hazard, as the driver and passengers may not be able to exit the vehicle quickly in an emergency situation.
symptoms: The passenger front seat fastens seatbelt signals when no one is in the front seat
the driver's door locks and won't unlock unless the remote is used
the breaks squeak only when exiting the garage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The phase-out of 3G technology and the lack of retrofitting by BMW can cause safety features to malfunction, including crash notifications and stolen vehicle recovery, making the vehicle more vulnerable to theft and accidents.
symptoms: The added safety features installed in the car are no longer working due to the 3G phase-out
the car has no space within the driver's sight to mount phones for directions/navigation
and voice activation/hand-free usage is disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine and transmission mounts can cause the engine and transmission to fall out of the vehicle, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Rattling sound from the center of the car
engine and transmission mounts collapsed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause injuries from shattered glass, distractions while driving, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Loud bang
broken glass
hole in the sunroof
glass protruding upwards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes gave out
car lunged forward at high speed
car switched modes by itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch actuator can cause doors to remain locked, trapping occupants in the event of an emergency.
symptoms: Inside door latches frequently do not open locked doors
must use power door unlock first.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drivetrain malfunction can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: "Drivetrain malfunction" message
car shuts down
replaced parts (fuel injector and module in fuel tank) did not resolve the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the main computer can cause the vehicle to lose all power, including emergency flashers, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Car went completely dead on the highway
main computer had a "catastrophic" failure.
